[h2 id=TricksAndTimesavers 
	" Tricks and timesavers
	$LF
]h2
[h3 id=BombsAsSteppingStones 
	" Bombs as stepping stones
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"Bombs are solid objects in all three directions and as such can be abused as movable platforms.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=UsingBombsToCrossTooWideGaps 
	" Using bombs to cross too wide gaps
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"Bombs can be placed misaligned to the game grid, meaning that you can shorten gaps with half a cell in some places.
	$LF
]div
[h4 id=51BossSkip 
	" 5-1 Boss skip
	$LF
]h4
[div class=p 
	"The hit region for the boss battle can be skipped by skipping across a bridge made out of bombs.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=GettingYourselfPlacedOnTopOfABomb 
	" Getting yourself placed on top of a bomb
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"With a little trickery it is possible to get yourself launched on top of a bomb on the same height level as you. This allows for great shortcuts by climbing stairs made out of bombs.
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=StunningPlayers 
	" Stunning players
	$LF
]h3
[div class=p 
	"If a player has a bomb placed on top of his head (usually from a throw) he will get stunned. Stunned players can be lifted up and thrown out of the stage. This is very efficient for getting rid of bosses.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"How-to:
	$LF
]div
[h3 id=BombTower 
	" Bomb-tower:
	$LF
]h3
[table 
	[tbody 
		[tr 
			[th 
				"Frame
			]th
			[th 
				"Input
			]th
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"1
			]td
			[td 
				"^99
			]td
			[th 
				" 
				[code 
					"(when Bomberman is going up)
				]code
				$LF
			]th
		]tr
		[tr 
			[td 
				"2
			]td
			[td 
